definition.value: A chromanone that is the 3,4-dihydro derivative of coumarin.
A beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
A gulonic acid formed by oxidising the aldehyde group of L-gulose to a carboxylic acid group.
A myo-inositol tetrakisphosphate having the phosphate groups placed at the 1-, 3-, 4- and 6-positions.
